14 (b) For plumber licenses, up to two (2) years; and
15 (c) For heating, ventilation, and air conditioning licenses, up to three thousand
16 (3,000) hours.
17 (3) The department shall establish a reporting system under this section through the
18 promulgation of administrative regulations in accordance with KRS Chapter
19 13A.
20 (4) The department shall utilize the current administrative regulations governing
21 licensure attainment to determine the eligibility and applicability of directly
22 related on-the-job training hours, ensuring alignment with existing licensure
23 requirements and standards.
